OL,3,CParents raise awareness of epilepsy
OL,4,Ccomplications after daughter's death
OL,6,FThe parents of a young woman with
OL,7,Fepilepsy who died suddenly are
OL,8,Fspeaking out about her death to raise
OL,9,Fawareness of the condition.
OL,11,FAmber Walker from Bournemouth, Dorset,
OL,12,Fdied from Sudden Unexpected Death in
OL,13,FEpilepsy (SUDEP) at the age of 22,
OL,14,Fafter being diagnosed when she was a
OL,15,Fteenager.
OL,17,FAccording to Oxfordshire charity SUDEP
OL,18,FAction, there is one death per 1,000
OL,19,Fpeople with epilepsy, per year.
